The paper discusses a method for autonomously learning interpretable policies for reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper uses genetic programming, which is a subfield of evolutionary computation, to learn policy equations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions an industrial benchmark, which suggests that it may fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY) as well. Finally, the paper uses neural networks as a baseline, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
